source.name: Measure 13   Percentage Of The Nonelderly Population With Health Insurance Coverage by Firm Size
source.description: Firm size: Individuals ages 0-64 are assigned to a firm size according to the largest sized employer of any non-elderly member of the family (defined as an adult, spouse, and dependent children.)  Individuals with no workers in their immediate family are excluded from this analysis.
